	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello all! I've been searching a lot about this, without any luck.
<br />
<br />I want to know if there is a way to make Famicom Disk System images (.fds files) from famicom or NES roms.
<br />
<br />My idea is to have a way to play roms on real hardware, using stuff I already have, a famicom, a FDS ram cart and a FDS-parallel cable, and also FDSloader of course.
<br />
<br />Is this possible? create FDS images from NES - FC ROMS? Even maybe many roms on one single FDS image, selectable with a menu, that'll be cool...
<br />
<br />Thanks you all in advance for all info you can give about this!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_cool.gif" alt="8)" title="Cool" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


